
[1]harsh

   H`ARSH, a.

   1. Rough to the touch; rugged; grating; as harsh sand; harsh cloth;
   opposed to smooth.

   2. Sour; rough to the taste; as harsh fruit.

   3. Rough to the ear; grating; discordant; jarring; as a harsh sound;
   harsh notes; a harsh voice.

   4. Austere; crabbed; morose; peevish. Civilization softens the harsh
   temper or nature of man.

   5. Rough; rude; abusive; as harsh words; a harsh reflection.

   6. Rigorous; severe.

   Though harsh the precept, yet the preacher charm'd.
